      <!-- ===================================================================
           SECTION: SHADCN COMPONENTS
           This section documents the shadcn/ui component layer and how brand
           tokens flow from Figma all the way to a production component.
           =================================================================== -->
      <section class="sg-section" id="basis-ui-components">
        <h2 class="sg-section-title">Basis UI Components</h2>
        <p class="sg-section-desc">
          Basis UI is a component library for Astro + Alpine.js built on the
          shadcn/ui convention. Components are not installed as a dependency —
          source lives in <code>src/components/ui/</code> and can be edited
          directly. Styling is driven entirely by CSS variables, so a single
          token change propagates to every component at once.
        </p>

        <h3 class="sg-subsection-title">The token pipeline</h3>
        <p class="sg-section-desc">
          Every color decision starts in Figma as a variable and ends up in a
          live component through a four-layer chain. Nothing is hardcoded at
          any step — a brand update touches one value and cascades everywhere.
        </p>
        <pre class="sg-code"><code>Step 1 — Figma variable (designer's source of truth)
         color/navy = #081F5D

Step 2 — Brand ramp token in global.css
         --navy-900: 223.8 84.2% 19.8%;  /* stored as HSL, no hsl() wrapper */

Step 3 — Semantic mapping in global.css (the bridge layer)
         --primary: 223.8 84.2% 19.8%;   /* "primary" maps to Deep Navy */
         --ring:    221.1 82.6% 36.1%;   /* focus rings use Navy 700 */

Step 4 — Basis UI component in Button.astro
         bg-primary   → resolves --primary → #081F5D in light mode
         hover:bg-ring → shifts to Navy 700 on focus/hover</code></pre>

        <h3 class="sg-subsection-title">What each variant controls</h3>
        <p class="sg-section-desc">
          Each shadcn variant maps to a different semantic token.
          Changing the token value updates the variant everywhere it is used —
          no per-component overrides needed.
        </p>
        <pre class="sg-code"><code>default   → bg-primary         (navy fill, white text)
outline   → border-border      (border stroke, no fill)
secondary → bg-secondary       (navy-100 tint surface)
ghost     → bg-transparent     (hover-only muted background)</code></pre>


